## Species

@fig-barplot-species is a bar plot of species of penguins.


::: {.cell fig.asp='0.618' output-location='column-fragment'}

```{.r .cell-code  code-line-numbers="|6|7-10"}
ggplot(
  penguins, 
  aes(x = species)
) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    x = "Species",
    y = "Count"
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Bar plot of species of penguins.](presentation_files/figure-revealjs/fig-barplot-species-1.png){#fig-barplot-species width=480}
:::
:::


## Penguins {.smaller}

@tbl-penguins shows the first 10 penguins from the dataset.


::: {#tbl-penguins .cell tbl-cap='First 10 penguins from the dataset.'}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true"}
penguins |>
  slice_head(n = 10) |>
  select(species, island, bill_length_mm, bill_depth_mm) |>
  gt()
```

